item.title: Help please
item.dc:creator: @johno2 johno2
item.description:
@johno2 wrote:

ok, go to your java versions, usally in c drive, then program files, java (right click windows bar and click explore, or open)

Ok it will say stuff like

jdk1.6.0_07

jre1.6.0_07

Thats your java versions, (you may have earlyer ones)

Now go to your compiler, right click and and click “edit” now look for a line what has

jdk1.6.0_07 (might be jdk1.6.0_07, jdk1.6.0_06, jdk1.6.0_05, jdk1.6.0_04, jdk1.6.0_03, jdk1.6.0_02, jdk1.6.0_01, or lower) now just edit to your java version
